FBIS4-30409 "dreas123__a94013" FBIS-EAS-94-123-A Daily Report 24 Jun 1994 ANNEX Japan Chief Cabinet Secretary on Monetary Intervention Chief Cabinet Secretary on Monetary Intervention OW2606195494 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 24 Jun 94 Evening Edition p 3 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW2606195494 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN Japanese BFN [Text] At a news conference after a 24 June cabinet meeting, Chief Cabinet Secretary Hiroshi Kumagai commented on the yen's rebound on New York Foreign Exchange Market, saying: "Finance Minister Hirohisa Fujii has also repeatedly said the government will deal with currency movements with a resolute attitude. We will maintain this attitude while considering a concerted intervention with other countries." He thus indicated a strong possibility of a concerted dollar-buying intervention in currency markets with the United States and European countries.
